        "commentary": "Rufus folding into Alexa+ signals **AMZN consolidating fragmented AI surfaces** — one assistant spanning shopping intent + smart-home + ambient compute. Strategic read: Amazon wants conversational commerce as the default discovery layer, bypassing Google Search. Watch ad-revenue mix shift if Rufus monetizes recommendations. Second-order: pressure on **GOOGL** Shopping ads and **SHOP**'s merchant-side AI (Sidekick), plus **WMT** (Sparky) and **TGT** must keep pace or cede share. Infra winners stay **NVDA** (inference GPUs) and **AVGO** (custom Trainium2/3 ASICs — Amazon's preferred path). Risk: Alexa+ monetization still unproven; integration could dilute Rufus's purchase-intent signal. Net: incremental AMZN positive, modest GOOGL/SHOP headwind, neutral-to-positive AI infra. Not binary — narrative reinforcement, not catalyst.",
